Feroxbuster
Fast content discovery tool written in Rust

Web Application
Description
Feroxbuster is a fast, recursive content discovery tool written in Rust. It is designed to perform forced browsing to find hidden directories and files on web servers.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which feroxbuster
Install command:

sudo apt install feroxbuster
Basic Syntax
feroxbuster -u <url>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
feroxbuster -u http://target.com

Basic scan	Find hidden dirs	
feroxbuster -u http://target.com -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt

Custom wordlist	Specific wordlist	
feroxbuster -u http://target.com -x php,html,txt

With extensions	Find specific files	
feroxbuster -u http://target.com --depth 3

Recursive depth	Deep discovery	
feroxbuster -u http://target.com -t 50

Set threads	Faster scanning	
feroxbuster -u http://target.com --filter-status 404

Filter status codes	Clean output	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Set target URL
2
Choose wordlist
3
Add file extensions
4
Run feroxbuster
5
Review discovered paths
Understanding the Output
Shows status codes, content length, and discovered URLs.

Important Warnings
•
Can generate heavy traffic
•
May trigger WAF/IDS
•
Use on authorized targets only
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
